#hm-note[
  *On Real Alchemy Ch. 2:* Bartlett introduces the philosophical framework with
  clarity suited to modern students. In particular, his treatment of the World Spirit
  and the Niter/Salt polarity at the close of the chapter anticipates Year Two and
  is worth flagging in the headmaster's mind, though students need not be directed
  to that section specifically until Year Two M04.

  *On GCH I, Ch. I–II:* These chapters are denser than anything in Albertus or
  Bartlett. Do not ask students to comprehend them fully on first reading. The
  instruction is to read and note what resonates or puzzles — comprehension will
  deepen through rereading across the curriculum.
]